  "prompt": "How do I recover my Gmail password with a recovery mobile number and a Gmail address?",
  "response": "To recover your Gmail password using a recovery mobile number and a recovery email address, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Gmail login page**: Visit [Gmail](http://mail.google.com).\n\n2. **Click on \u201cForgot password?\u201d**: This link is typically located beneath the password field.\n\n3. **Enter your email address**: Type in the email address you are trying to recover and click \"Next\".\n\n4. **Verify your identity**:\n   - You might be asked to enter the last password you remember. If you don\u2019t remember, click \u201cTry another way\u201d.\n   \n5. **Use recovery options**:\n   - **Via recovery email**: You will be sent a verification code to your recovery email address. Enter the code and follow the instructions to reset your password.\n   - **Via recovery mobile number**: You will receive a verification code via SMS to your recovery mobile number. Enter the code and follow the instructions to reset your password.\n\n6. **Set a new password**: Once verified through your recovery options, you can set a new password. Ensure your new password is strong (a mix of letters, numbers, and special characters).\n\n7. **Update recovery options**: After you regain access to your account, it\u2019s wise to check and update your recovery options to ensure they are correct and current.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during the process, Google provides a series of additional steps for account recovery, such as answering security questions or providing additional information you might remember. Follow the prompts and provide as much accurate information as possible.\n\nRemember to secure your account further by enabling two-factor authentication (2FA) once you regain access.",
